CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 30, 1960, pg. A1 reads: "Filthy 'Eyesore' - This debris-cluttered area in middle of the 2100 block of Wylie Ave., has persisted for more than a month and a half. It is not only an "eyesore" to residents and passersby, but it constitutes a health hazard, particularly during these hot and humid days.  Neighbors' complaints apparently have fallen on deaf ears in City Hall and in the county.  The Health Department needs to have a look and take immediate action. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two women, one holding hat box, standing in front of empty lot between two brick buildings with trash and rubble, 2100 block of Wylie Avenue, Hill District, another version
